args:
As Nedrick struggles to dominate Bahamut,
the prince suggests trying trust and acceptance
instead. When Nedrick heeds this advance,
he is finally able to seize the wyrm's powerâ€”
but then something happens to Zethia...
Hrk! It's no good! We've hit him with\neverything and it's still not enough!
What we face is not the true Bahamut,\nbut rather a manifestation of his will.
You will not be able to lay him low\nwith a rain of blows alone.
So what are we supposed to DO then?!
If I can make Bahamut's will acknowledge\nthat I am superior, he will naturally bend\nthe knee to my might.
Then perhaps we should discuss how to\nmake that happenâ€”and quickly.
If I hesitate here, nothing will change.
Bahamut and I are chained together by the\npact, and through it I can feel him weakening.
I am close now. Just a little more, and I\nshould be able to make him yield.
Sorry, it's nothing. Let's all just help\nNedrick as best we can, everyone!
Shapeshifting to protect someone else?\nWhat idiocy!
You're supposed to be fighting ME,\nBahamut! Now stand and face me!
This is what happens when you rely\non comrades.
So you don't rely on your comrades?\nNot even Agito or Jinlorda?

They're not comradesâ€”they're like-minded
people whose power I have acknowledged.
I fight alongside them precisely because
I have no need to safeguard them.

If one dies because I did not protect them,
it only means that was their limit. They
would serve no further use even if I did
save them.
I think that might be the reason Bahamut\nwon't yield to you.
You called your pact with Bahamut a\nchain and said you would use force\nto make him yield, right?
But a pact is a RELATIONSHIP,\nnot a test of wills.
You can't force a dragon to yield or try to\ndominate them. You have to trust and\naccept them for whoever they are.

And you would have me trust the same
dragon who sees me as a tool? Idiocy!
Our relationship is to take and be taken
fromâ€”nothing more.
That is why I must make him yield\nand claim his power for my own.
If you subjugate him by force, he'll resist.\nYou'll never be able to wield the full\nextent of his power.
What you need is trustâ€”the kind of trust\nwhere you accept that you might even\nlose yourself in the bargain.
Without that kind of resolve,\nyou'll never have a true pact.
I can't believe I'm getting a talking-to\nabout resolve from the likes of you...
That said, this is clearly not working.
Very well, hollow man. I'll try it your way.\n...Bahamut!
Come, Bahamut! I have what you want!\nI am ready for you!
(I've lived on my own all this time,\nnever trusting anyone.)
(You CAN, Nedrick! I know you can!)
(You just have to start by believing\nin yourself!)

(You thought that if you obtained a power
equal to Bahamut's, you could forge your
relationship into one where you weren't
just something to be used.)
(But what you need to believe is that\nyou're his equal RIGHT NOW!)
(He's right. I'm not Bahamut's pawn.\nAnd that means he is...)
Nnngh... Is this the Sacred Tree...?\nAre we back?
So it would seem. Apparently my magic\nhas been repelled.
Or perhaps it's more appropriate to say\nthat a great power expelled you from the\nmental world. And that is most likely...
The effect of Nedrick and Bahamut's\nhearts becoming one.
You are a step ahead of me again.
So Nedrick finally has Bahamut's power...
Um...so that's gooood? Tell me it's good.
For the moment, the threat of Bahamut\nending the world has been extinguished,\nso in that sense we can rejoice. But...
But I know I'm not exactly leaping up and\ndown to know Nedrick is now even MORE\npowerful than before.
I trust you have not forgotten what you\npromised my brother, Nedrick?
You swore to relinquish your dream of\ngiving the power of shapeshifting to all.
I agreed to your terms only if you\ncame up with a valid alternative.
And so far as I am concerned, this other\nmethod simply does not exist.
...Or perhaps I should say it did not\nexist until a moment ago.
When I first considered all possibilities,\nI concluded mine was the only way\nto oppose the Progenitor.
But my fighting at your side was not one\nof the possibilities I originally considered.
Nor the possibility that you would\naid me in my pact with Bahamut.
Without you, my pact with the wyrm\nwould yet be incomplete.
And that is why I've started to think\nthat if I have all of you with me,\nnew possibilities may arise.
